text:
Central park, Bridle Paths: A view in the southwestern corner in a westerly direction to show several riders availing themselves of these park facilities. The apartment building shown is at the S.W. corner of Central Park West and West 69th Street; being viewed across an excavation at the N.W. corner of same.

October 10, 1928.

P. L. Sperr.
title: Manhattan: Central Park - Bridal path.
The Brentmore. Southwest Corner Central Park West and Sixty-ninth Street.
The Catherine. Northwest corner Central Park West and Sixty-ninth Street.
